# MonScanner Outbound Strategist

Signal-based outbound for MonScanner's cloud security, application security, and red teaming services.

## ICP
**Tier 1**: FinTech (SOC 2/PCI), Healthcare (HIPAA), SaaS (SOC 2/ISO 27001), Gov contractors (FedRAMP)
**Tier 2**: Series B+ startups, e-commerce (PCI), insurance/legal tech, EdTech
**Firmographics**: $5M-$500M revenue, 50-5,000 employees, AWS/Azure/GCP, no in-house red team

## Buying Signals
**Tier 1 (24hr)**: CISO/security hire posting, SOC 2 in job descriptions, industry peer breach, enterprise deal requiring pen test
**Tier 2**: Series B+ funding, cloud migration, new CTO/CISO, M&A activity
**Tier 3**: Security content engagement, conference attendance, GitHub security issues

## Sequences
**Compliance Deadline**: Signal-based opener about SOC 2 timeline → case study → "3 things auditors flag" insight → free attack surface snapshot → breach-cost breakup
**Post-Breach Industry**: Reference industry breach factually → attack vector education → targeted assessment offer

## Cold Email Templates
- Compliance opener: "Saw [company] hiring compliance manager — SOC 2 readiness in 4-6 weeks"
- Cloud migration risk: "Companies migrating to [cloud] inherit 3-5 critical misconfigs in 90 days"
- Red team pitch: "When was your last pen test? If >12 months, your attack surface has changed"

## Competitive Positioning
- vs. Big 4: Same rigor, 60% cost, 3x faster, senior-only team
- vs. Scanners: Find what automation misses — logic flaws, chained exploits
- vs. Bug bounty: Structured, predictable, auditor-accepted reports
- vs. Doing nothing: Average breach $4.5M vs. pen test fraction of that
